The paper discusses user studies on the cognitive burden and expressiveness of different representations of attribute-level uncertainty in on-demand curation (ODC) tools. This involves evaluating the effectiveness of UI design guidelines and best practices for conveying uncertainty in ODC systems. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Databases (cs.DB) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) since the paper deals with data quality and curation. Additionally, Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) could also be relevant categories since they deal with uncertainty and data interpretation.
